 <text>
  <front>
   <head>TO LOTHARIO.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">not, Lothario, while I view</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The bright expression of thy face,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And on thy cheek of crimson hue</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Emotion's varying beauties trace,</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">That in my heart one feeling dwells,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But what the coldest must approve,</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Nor think my conscious bosom swells</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">With aught resembling secret love.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">No .... still these eyes can fix on thine,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Nor fear their keenest glance to meet;</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And when thou boldly searchest mine,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">My quiet heart disdains to beat.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But, if by vain self-love misled,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Thou in my looks canst passion see;</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And think, by weak illusions fed,</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">My towering hopes aspire to thee ....</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="5" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="17" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Let us my absent Henry seek;</l>
     <l n="18" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And when he meets my conscious eyes,</l>
     <l n="19" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">In every glance my heart will speak,</l>
     <l n="20" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And plainly tell for whom it sighs.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
